{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idbf663324-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s12205"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"12205"},"text":"§ 12205.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Attorney’s fees","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In any action or administrative proceeding commenced pursuant to this chapter, the court or agency, in its discretion, may allow the prevailing party, other than the United States, a reasonable attorney’s fee, including litigation expenses, and costs, and the United States shall be liable for the foregoing the same as a private individual.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idbf663325-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/336/tV/s505"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–336, title V, § 505","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-07-26"},"text":"July 26, 1990","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/104/371"},"text":"104 Stat. 371","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idbf663326-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idbf663327-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idbf663328-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This chapter, referred to in text, was in the original “this Act”, meaning ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/336"},"text":"Pub. 